This was the most frustrating experience I've had with a doctor's office.  You will not be able to speak to a human when you call and it will take you hours to chase after them to get someone to respond to you.  Who has an entire day to spend leaving messages, sending emails, and continue calling until you actually get to speak to someone?  Then, when you do get someone, their attitudes are rude and not helpful.  Overall, it was an unpleasant experience to waste so much time dealing with them.
Doctor Hamat and the whole clinic staff was excellent.

We called to let them know we were on our way because our previous dr’s appointment took longer than expected.apparently they never got the message. At arrival we felt the mistreatment as we were asked, in a very rude manner, three times why we came in late. We let them know we called ahead to tell we were on our way. We even left a message at the office manager’s ph. The lady that initially took care of us was upset. Then came the registered nurse who was actually kind at the beginning. My husband asked for permission from her to attend an urgent call from work. Permission was acknowledged by registered nurse. The registered nurse after explaining the process got upset when we asked, in a very kind and sweet manner,  when the Md would take care of us. She said in a very upset voice the appointment was with her, got up from her chair and slammed the door. Never came back. After a while , The First Lady, entry data professional,  came in and was not much nicer when we explained no one told us we were not to be seen by an MD. We even apologized for asking where was the Doctor. We just made a simple question , though we were very appreciative of the registered nurse knowledge and professional explanation of the procedure. We actually left very much mistreated, discriminated against and feeling worse than when we went in. We paid for a Dr’s appointment, and came out while the data entry professional nodded her head, no prescription, no medical procedure.   We have no doubt of their knowledge, professionalism and care, however their manners are not the best.

Katie Bycura is the absolute best!  I had chronic diarrhea for 20 years.  I’ve seen 2 gastroenterologists and 2 internists.  None helped me.  Katie listened to all my symptoms, asked questions about past antibiotic use, and sent me for a special test:  hydrogen breath test.  Finally I had a diagnosis: small intestine bacterial overgrowth, or SIBO.  There’s only 1 antibiotic that cures it.  Katie was able to get me the antibiotic after Medicare denied it.  I am now symptom free.  After 20 years!

Lady at the front desk lacks sensitivity and manners. My husband had an appointment yesterday.m with Katie (PA. )I asked if I could come in with him since he has onset Alzheimer’s. She told me “no, covid regulations” I tried to explain to her that he forgets details and I had to be there with him. Again, she said “no”!  After my husband came out of the appointment, I asked him if everything went ok. He said he “thought “ it did. We proceed it to make a follow up appointment. At that time, I asked the same woman receptionist to please write down on my husband’s records that he has memory problems and therefore, I have to come   in with him. She replied “No one other than the patient is allowed to go in and you need to prove to me that he has Alzheimer’s”!!!! I told her that on his records says that he takes meds for his memory and that I WOULD NEVER lie about my husband having such a sad condition. I’m the receptionist replied again that Katie (PA) doesn’t make the rules because she is “just “ another worker there!  There is NO WAY that I am taking my husband back there. Such an insensitive person working with patients!! Please don’t take your loved ones ..especially, if they have some type of condition where they need a family member present to ask questions, to take notes et. We like Katie but that front desk person needs training to be more courteous

As many have said, Dr. Reddy and Laura Peterkin are great- no issues there. Again, as others have said, the back office staff, the response time to messages, the info that comes from the office staff is horrendous. When I retired, I had 14-15 individuals that reported to me over the years on my staff. If any of them did some of things this staff does in terms of what I mentioned, they wouldn’t have worked alongside me. Thought: maybe the timing problems, the messaging problems, the communication problems, etc are all due to the age of the equipment and system used in the office. I say this because the problems today are the same as 20 years ago. Finally, get rid of that music you play when people are holding. That stuff is annoying.

I’m hesitant to post a review as I am still a patient but here goes anyway.

I absolutely love Katie and cannot say enough great things about her.  She makes me feel reassured and that she really wants to help me.  I believe she really cares.  It comes through in her work, attitude and smile.  She takes the time to explain things and go over all the options.  I never feel rushed but I’m respectful of her time.

With that being said, I agree with some of the comments in other reviews.  They do not answer the phone and return messages promptly.  I’ve  been dealing with a member of the office staff who probably shouldn’t be answering the phone/questions.  She’s very curt and always sounds mad.  I don’t doubt that she’s knowledgeable but she seems to dislike answering questions and relating to patients.  I’ve spoken to her about 3 or 4 times during treatment and my last phone conversation was not contentious or angry but she hung up without saying bye.  I thought that was weird. If she didn’t have such a sour attitude I might have written it off as an accident.

I give the practice 4 stars because of the doctors and Katie.  I honestly can’t give it 5 because of the staff.  They could improve in customer service and empathy.  Whether they know it or not, that comes across loud and clear even over the phone.

I wanted to rave about how great this location is.  They helped me with all my needs.  The front desk was especially excellent a beautiful lady named Tiffany Donley.  The physician Katy Bycura was very thorough and made me feel like I was part of the family.  I would recommend this location to anyone that wants excellent service.

The office personal is horrible and will go to another Dr for my questions. They canceled my appointment once and tried to reschedule me again. But the worst part of it, was when I finally got there and saw the Dr. ,  she was not given all of my paperwork from my blood test that I brought with me for my questions. I was asked to give the lady at the front my lab results and the main page that I needed for my questions was not given to her. And she said she would check for me but never did! When I went to front desk I asked for it and the lady got very rude with me, like she had no concern for my health! I told her that’s why I went there is for a specialist to answer my question. So the problem was, is that the lady in front did not give the Dr all my paperwork ! She was extremely rude with an evil face towards me! How do you work in this field and do not care about people?! So now I have wasted my money and time and will have to find another Dr. This place is a total joke and will never go back!!

I wish I could award 5 stars. If this review were based only on medical providers, I would. Dr. Reddy and his PA Laura P. are excellent, skilled, caring, competent professionals. Unfortunately, my experience with the billing/insurance department has been less than satisfactory. For the visit 1/17, I received a claim in the mail for an insurance company I do not even have! Even though I provided correct updated information prior to my visit and my updated cards at the visit. No one has explained the issue. I would like an explanation to set my mind at ease. Additionally, the billing department is VERY hard to reach. When I finally did so, the person was very  nice, but had no idea as to why the problem came about. When I brought the document by the Pine Croft office today, 2/19/20, the front desk staff was less than reassuring. Additionally, I had made a followup appointment for 2 weeks after a procedure. My doctor recommended a 3 month followup. So I changed the appointment, but continued to receive email reminders for the  cancelled appointment.
Update 2/21/20 Teresa, the billing manager called today and reassured me all is well. I appreciated that so very much.
Update 3/5/20
I was assured by Teresa, the billing manager, that my insurance issues were resolved. Unfortunately that is not the case. I received a bill that they clearly filed on the wrong insurance. So frustrating. It messes up my deductible issue when visiting other providers. I am VERY frustrated and angry. If someone would have had the courtesy to research this issue and contact me, I'd really appreciate it.
3/9/20
Michelle had emailed me Friday. I just called spoke to her. She explained the issue and assured me everything was taken care of. I appeciate so much the time it took to thoroughly explain the issue.

The office is HORRIBLE.  You can NEVER get anyone to answer the phone or call you back.  I have called, left messages, emailed.  It is the worst customer service I have ever experienced from a medical office.  The doctors are great, but they need to greatly improve the office.
Ask for Tiffany. She is very helpful. Took the time to answer my many questions and made me feel comfortable.

Will go to no other doctor in this field, but Dr. Hamat.
Recommend him to all that have GI problems.
